These equations are satisfied when (x=0,y=0)
is mapped to 
.if n \
(r=0,theta=0)
.if t \
(r=0,\(*h=0)
on a VAX.  In general, conversions to polar coordinates
should be computed thus:
.nf
.ta 1iR +1n +\w' := hypot(x,y);'u+0.5i
.if n \{\
	r	:= hypot(x,y);	... := sqrt(x\(**x+y\(**y)
